title: SFH on redevelopment of hospitals
content_text:
p>
	Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for Food and 
	Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, after attending a public function this afternoon 
	(July 13): Reporter: (On the redevelopment of Queen Mary Hospital) Secretary for Food and Health: We welcome the funding approval (by the 
	Finance Committee of the Legislative Council) for the redevelopment plan of 
	Queen Mary Hospital. This is very important as we all know that Queen Mary 
	Hospital is an important teaching and acute general hospital for the Hong

Hospital is an important teaching and acute general hospital for the Hong 
	Kong West Cluster of Hospital Authority. We thank the chairperson as well as 
	members of the Finance Committee in expediting the deliberations and 
	approval for the redevelopment project of Queen Mary Hospital. At the same 
	time, I am very concerned about and disappointed on the general progress of 
	deliberations at various subcommittees as well as the Legislative Council 
	itself. In particular, there is another development project under the 
	Hospital Authority, that is the redevelopment of Hong Kong Buddhist

Hospital Authority, that is the redevelopment of Hong Kong Buddhist 
	Hospital, being stuck in the Public Works Subcommittee of the Legislative 
	Council. Practically, there will be with little hope that the project could 
	go through all the funding approval procedures in this legislative year. 
	Re-tendering of the redevelopment project of Hong Kong Buddhist Hospital is 
	now unavoidable and delay in the redevelopment progress as well as 
	escalation in project costs might also be resulted. (Please also refer to the
escalation in project costs might also be resulted. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.)
